Version 0.0.14 (11 April 2016)
--------------

	metadata.json: permit the extension to be loaded by
	gnome-shell-3.18.

Version 0.0.13 (16 October 2015)
--------------

	metadata.json: permit the extension to be loaded by
	gnome-shell-3.18.

Version 0.0.12 (3 April 2015)
--------------

	metadata.json: permit the extension to be loaded by
	gnome-shell-3.16.

Version 0.0.11 (24 October 2014)
--------------

	metadata.json: permit the extension to be loaded by
	gnome-shell-3.14.

Version 0.0.10 (4 April 2014)
--------------

	metadata.json: permit the extension to be loaded by
	gnome-shell-3.12.

Version 0.0.9 (22 October 2013)
-------------

	extension.js, metadata.json: convert the extension for use with
	gnome-shell-3.10.

	po/hu_HU.po, po/LINGUAS, locale/hu_HU/LC_MESSAGES/favorites.mo:
	add Hungarian translation (Zoltan Riba).

Version 0.0.8 (12 April 2013)
-------------

	org.gnome.shell.extensions.favorites.gschema.xml, extension.js,
	prefs.js, metadata.json, stylesheet.css, favorites.pot, en_GB.po:
	convert the extension for use with gnome-shell-3.8 (preferences
	for the extension can now only be changed via the gnome shell
	extensions preferences dialog, gnome-tweak-tool or dconf, because
	gnome-shell-3.8 does not permit the pull-down menu to delete and
	then reinsert itself).

Version 0.0.7 (8 January 2013)
-------------

	extension.js: prevent timer callback executing after the system
	calls disable() immediately after calling enable (thanks to Norman
	Smith for debugging this one.)

Version 0.0.6 (7 October 2012)
-------------

	extension.js, metadata.json: convert the extension for use with
	gnome-shell-3.6.  This includes adopting the new public interface
	for adding items to the panel, which in turn requires destroying
	and reconstructing the favorites button when the user moves it
	postion on the panel.

Version 0.0.5 (15 July 2012)
-------------

	extension.js, prefs.js, po/favorites.pot, po/en_GB.po,
	schemas/org.gnome.shell.extensions.favorites.gschema.xml: use
	GSettings to save preferences, and provide the option of using
	gnome-shell-extension-prefs only to set preferences (so allowing
	the preferences entry in the drop-down menu to be removed).

	README: add README file.

Version 0.0.4 (24 April 2012)
-------------

	extension.js, metadata.json: convert the extension for use with
	gnome-shell-3.4.

Version 0.0.3 (11 March 2012)
-------------

	extension.js, stylesheet.css, po/favorites.pot, po/en_GB.po:
	enable the user to select the position of the panel icon in the
	left panel box, by means of the Preferences item of the drop-down
	menu.

Version 0.0.2 (8 March 2012)
-------------

	ChangeLog: add this ChangeLog file.

	extension.js: move setting of textdomain from enable() function to
	init() function and use the gnome-shell-3.2 extension system to
	find the locale path.

	extension.js: obtain favorites list by using higher level
	appFavorites functions instead of going directly to GSettings.

	extension.js: extract the value of FAVORITE_APPS_KEY from the
	appFavorites object rather than reinventing it ourselves.

	extension.js, stylesheet.css, po/favorites.pot, po/en_GB.po:
	provide an option to display the panel button with an icon instead
	of text.

Version 0.0.1 (27 December 2011)
-------------

	Initial release
